div.p:
or, to speak more
properly, stays me here at
home unkept;

and if it please your
ladyships, you may see the
end;

I shall do my friends no
wrong, for I have none to
lament me;

whose loves are dearer
than the natural bond of
sisters;

"Aye," quoth Jaques,
"Sweep on, you fat and
greasy citizens;

Ah, we that are true
lovers run into strange
capers;

seeking the bubble
reputation even in the
cannon's mouth;

if thou never sawest good
manners, thy manners must be
wicked;
